did.abstract: This collection contains correspondence, memorandums, conference materials, notes, chapters from novels, pieces of news, obituaries, and photographs relating to the International Brotherhood of Teamsters amassed by member Leo Deaner. The materials date from 1902 to 2006.
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged into eighteen subject series: James R. Hoffa, Teamsters History, Teamsters Leaders, Contracts and Agreements, Project RISE, Personal/Family Files, Pennsylvania Local Unions, Conventions, Local Union Trusteeships, Yager-Kaiser Hearings, John Morris/Local 115, Lyndon LaRouche, Hamilton Trial Transcripts, Ron Carey Investigation, Miscellaneous Research Files, Notes and Subject Binders, and James P. Hoffa.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, memorandums, conference materials, notes, chapters from novels, pieces of news, obituaries, and photographs relating to the International Brotherhood of Teamsters amassed by member Leo Deaner. The materials date from 1902 to 2008.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials of this series include correspondence, memorandums, conference materials, notes, chapters from novels, pieces of news, and photographs. The series is maintained the order in which it was received; the beginning of the series is chronological, followed by photographs of Hoffa in various places.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries compromises the administrative files, official correspondence, and internal financial records of Local 776 officials, including those of Charles Leo Deaner. It ranges from early 1940 to 1993. Materials include internal and external correspondence of Charles Leo Deaner, his personal notes, Local 776's financial statements, administrative logs, newsclippings, and membership surveys. It also includes historical audio-visual items such as film reels and videocassettes.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains the Teamsters' National Master Freight Agreements dating from 1964-1998, as well as Central Pennsylvania area supplemental agreements for these years. It also contains pre-National Master Freight agreements for IBT Local 776, Joint Council 53 and the Eastern Conference of Teamsters dating back to 1942. Completing the subseries are booklets, news clippings, correspondence, bulletins, flyers and other material related to agreement negotiation and contract ratification, including material covering the 1994 Teamsters strike.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains Teamsters' contracts with the United Parcel Service, Inc. (UPS) dating from 1970-2002, as well as materials related to the negotiation of these agreements spanning the same years. These include contract proposals, ballots and voting results, supplemental agreements, reports, news clippings, newsletters, news releases, correspondence and e-mails, among a variety of other material. Much of the material relates to IBT Local 776. and other Pennsylvania Teamsters, specifically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains multiple drafts of Project RISES' Code of Conduct, developed as a set of standards for the Teamsters to avoid the "plague of corruption" and the "intrusion of politics into Union discipline." The drafts span 13 months of development and revision, and include official drafts, confidential drafts, and "red-line" drafts (direct comparisons between two documents). Some correspondence also accompanies most drafts.Topics covered in the Code include expenditure of union money, local union elections, and political activity, as well as proposed enforecement mechanisms.

did.unittitle: The Teamsters and Organized Crime Report

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains drafts and final copies of a report, commissioned by Project RISE and prepared by the law firm Stier, Anderson & Malone, LLC, on the history and perception of organized crime's influence on the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. Included are the main text of the report as well as public and confidential appendices. Over 500 pages long and split into 26 chapters, the report covers the entire history of the Teamsters, the state of organized crime in the union at the time of writing, and recommendations to Project RISE about how to run a clean union in the future.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains Leo Deaner's personal and family-related files. The included materials date from 1937-2007 and mostly cover Deaner's family history, with a particular focus on his father, IBT Local 776 member Charles E. Deaner. Specific materials contained in the series include numerous photographs, correspondence, news clippings, collected family documents (e.g. birth/death certificates), IBT Local 776 history, and company history. Also included are various pieces of ephemera mostly related to Charles Deaner, including safe driver cards and pins, convention delegate pins and ribbons, awards, and Deaner's World War II dog tags.
